benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/admin/healthcheck - Put the host out of rotation

covered: Valid Deletion: TC01 demonstrates successful deletion and host out of rotation.
Authorization: TC02 and TC03 cover unauthorized access handling with 401 responses.
Concurrency: TC11 tests concurrent DELETE requests and proper handling.
Error Handling: TC04 (host already out of rotation), TC05 (service down), TC06 (system error), TC09 (invalid body), TC07 (method not allowed) cover various error responses.
Performance: TC10 and TC11 cover response time requirements under normal and concurrent conditions.
Regression: TC12 ensures the previously fixed issue remains resolved.
Security: TC13 tests injection-like header handling and authentication considerations.
Edge Case: TC14 handles the scenario with no hosts in rotation.
gaps: Non-Existent Resource: No explicit test for attempting to delete when there is no corresponding resource/host (beyond “no hosts in rotation” scenario).
Soft Deletes: No test verifying whether deletion is soft or hard, or what “out of rotation” status implies in data persistence.
Rate Limiting: No tests on handling multiple requests in quick succession beyond general concurrency.
Caching Behavior: No tests around caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) or related client-side caching behavior.
Authorization Granularity: Only 401 cases covered; no explicit 403 for authenticated-but-not-authorized scenarios.
recommendations: Add a test for deleting when the target resource is non-existent or already deleted (explicit Non-Existent Resource case).
Add a Soft Delete vs Hard Delete clarification test to verify how “out of rotation” is persisted and reflected in data models.
Introduce Rate Limiting tests to validate throttling or queueing under burst loads.
Add tests for caching behavior (ETag, Cache-Control) and ensure proper caching semantics.
Consider adding an explicit 403 Forbidden test for authenticated users lacking sufficient permissions.
